It is a behavioral pattern
- It defines a group of classes that represent a set of possible behaviors that can be plugged into an application, changing the
functionality on the fly
- It allows changing the behavior of an object dynamicallywithout changing the object itself
- Strategies provide a way to configure one class with manybehaviors when
- related classes differ only in their behavior
- an algorithm must be selected at run-time
- want to add to the possible ways to perform an action